race.comment: TAKE ACHANCE ON ME (3) had been plying her trade in harder NSW contests before hitting the frame at the Gold Coast last time out in a career-best performance. Ready to peak now third-up from the break and must be respected from the Waller yard. Goes on top. The well-related HIGHGROVE ROSE (7) (half to G2 winner Not An Option) got up to Listed level in her first preparation and should find this assignment much more to her liking. In the mix. MISSISSIPPI DREAM (2) hasn't shown much in both starts to date but gets the reliable Vandyke/Maloney combination and sharp improvement would not surprise. KOBABILITY (9) next in line with the 2kg claim.
